For + -ing

We use for + -ing when we want to talk about the purpose of something - the reason why something is used.

The bookshelf is for storing my books. 
(Q. Why do you have a bookshelf?) 
(A. For storing my books - so this is the reason or purpose of the bookshelf)

It is for hanging my clothes.
I don't use my tablet for writing emails.
The hairdryer is for drying my hair.

What is this money for?
It's for spending on vacation.

Note: We use the infinite if we want to talk about the purpose of someone or something 
I use the hairdryer to dry my hair.
